---
import eoh_png from '../../assets/images/eoh.png';
import '../../styles/arrow.css';
---

<section 
    id="landing_page" 
    data-color="var(--color-blue)" 
    class="color-section h-[calc(100vh-var(--nav-height))] w-full flex flex-col items-stretch overflow-hidden snap-start md:flex-row md:items-end"
    style="scroll-margin-top: var(--nav-height);"
>

    <!-- Text section -->
    <div class="w-full flex-1 px-[3.5vw] pb-[2vh] order-1 flex flex-col justify-center md:h-full md:pl-[1.5vw] md:pb-[3vh] md:order-2 md:flex-1 md:justify-end">
        <div class="flex flex-col mb-4 md:mb-6">
            <span class="block text-sm md:text-lg">Coming Soon</span>
            <span class="block text-sm font-bold md:text-lg -mt-1">Behold the Man</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[11px] text-xs leading-relaxed md:text-sm">
            As a teenager I learned that desire can also be a wound. I aim to capture that instant: when the body learns devotion and dread in the same breath.
            <br/>
            Adolescence arrives as the body awakens, a founding moment when desire can be an experience of the sacred, or an omen of death. The film observes that threshold, giving it a place and form.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Image section -->
    <div class="w-full h-auto shrink-0 order-2 flex items-end overflow-hidden md:w-auto md:h-full md:mt-0 md:order-1">
        <img 
            src={eoh_png.src} 
            alt="Eis o Homem - Still" 
            class="w-full h-auto object-contain block m-0 md:w-auto md:h-full" 
            />
    </div>

    <!-- Animated arrow -->
    <div class="absolute bottom-4 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 pointer-events-none flex justify-center items-center">
        <div class="line-container">
            <div class="line"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    /* Optional: Scale down the arrow slightly for mobile */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .arrow-down {
            transform: scale(0.7);
            bottom: 10px;
        }
    }
</style>